Implement the approved specification found under $SOLO_SPEC_DIR (spec.md and the feature files) against task.md: change the code so ./test.sh passes, and commit the result on the current git branch (do not switch branches, do not touch task.md or test.sh). Run the quality gates through the wrappers at the paths in the environment variables $CRAFT_CRAP and $CRAFT_DRY, invoked by their absolute path on your changed files (e.g. "$CRAFT_CRAP" sut.sh and "$CRAFT_DRY" sut.sh) — use ONLY these wrappers, never a language quality tool directly and never any mutation testing.
